Decolorization was analyzed spectrophotometrically using a UV-vis spectrophotometer (Varian Cary 100, USA). To measure the amount of color removal, samples (1.5 ml) of the culture media were withdrawn at regular time intervals, well agitated before sampling and centrifuged at 7500 rpm for five minutes with a micro refrigerated centrifuge (Hettich, Micro 200R, Germany) at 20 °C to gain clear supernatant. The following equation was used to calculate the decolorization rate:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
